<div class="container" id="notebook-container">
        
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Purpose of notebook: "Mahalanobis distance based on the Fisher information can be viewed as an approximation to the KL divergence between two distributions, as we verify mathematically and empirically below. This is the basis for natural gradient method."</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Theory">Theory<a class="anchor-link" href="#Theory"> </a></h2><p>Result:</p>
<p>{% raw %}
$$D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta'}) \approx \frac{1}{2} (\theta' - \theta)^T F(\theta) (\theta' - \theta)$$
{% endraw %}</p>
<p>Derivation:</p>
<p>Do second-order Taylor expansion of $D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, q_{\theta'})$ around $\theta' = \theta$. The key is to think of $\theta$ as a constant, and $\theta'$ as the variable.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
$$
D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta'}) 
\approx
\underbrace{D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta})}_{0}
+ (\theta' - \theta)^T \underbrace{\nabla_{\theta'} D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta'}) \mid_{\theta'=\theta}}_{\text{gradient}}
+ \frac{1}{2} (\theta' - \theta)^T \underbrace{\nabla^2_{\theta'} D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta'}) \mid_{\theta'=\theta}}_{\text{hessian}} (\theta' - \theta)
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Now, let's keep expanding the gradient and the hessian.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The gradient turns out to be the expected value of the score function, which is zero.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
$$
\begin{aligned}
\nabla_{\theta'} D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta'}) \mid_{\theta'=\theta}
&amp; = \nabla_{\theta'} \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} [\log p_\theta (x) - log p_{\theta'} (x)] \mid_{\theta'=\theta} \\
&amp; = \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} [0 - \nabla_{\theta'} log p_{\theta'} (x) \mid_{\theta'=\theta} ] \\
&amp; = - \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} [\nabla_{\theta'} log p_{\theta'} (x) \mid_{\theta'=\theta} ] \\
&amp; = 0
\end{aligned}
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The Hessian turns out to be the negative hessian of NLL and hence the Fisher information (which can be approximated using Monte-Carlo):</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
$$
\begin{aligned}
\nabla_{\theta'}^2 D_{KL}(p_{\theta}, p_{\theta'}) \mid_{\theta'=\theta}
&amp; = \nabla_{\theta'}^2 \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} [\log p_\theta (x) - log p_{\theta'} (x)] \mid_{\theta'=\theta} \\
&amp; = \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} [0 - \nabla_{\theta'}^2 log p_{\theta'} (x) \mid_{\theta'=\theta} ] \\
&amp; = - \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} [\nabla_{\theta'}^2 log p_{\theta'} (x) \mid_{\theta'=\theta} ] &amp;&amp; \text{negative Hessian of NLL}\\
&amp; = \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x} \sim p_{\mathbf{\theta}}} \left[(\nabla_{\theta'} log p_{\theta'} (x) \mid_{\theta'=\theta}) (\nabla_{\theta'} log p_{\theta'} (x) \mid_{\theta'=\theta})^T \right] &amp;&amp; \text{Fisher information}\\
&amp; = F(\theta)
\end{aligned}
$$
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Putting everything together, we have the result stated earlier.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
